cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is primarily focused on language modelling, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses reinforcement learning (RL) and object matching tasks, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions speech modelling, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the speech is being analyzed visually.
